Jan Nissar Akhtar Khan lives a poor life-style with his wife Zakhiya and small daughter. He is the sole bread winner for his family who is entrapped in a racket by a smuggler by the name of Mr. Ram Gupta; in this racket Khan is arrested and subsequently imprisoned. Unable to bear living in a society who holds Khan guilty, Zakhiya and her small daughter decide to commit suicide. Years later Khan is released from jail after serving penance and begins to fend for himself until he meets another young man, Vijay Kumar Singh, who swears to avenge the death of his family members against three men Amar, Akbar and Anthony. Written by gavin (&lt;a class=&quot;__cf_email__&quot; href=&quot;/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection&quot; data-cfemail=&quot;f58794969e819a9ab59d9a8198949c99db969a98&quot;&gt;[email&amp;#160;protected]&lt;/a&gt;&lt;script cf-hash='f9e31' type=&quot;text/javascript&quot;&gt;
